{
  "texts": [
    "By utilizing vector representations of words, we can train NNs on large text corpora, allowing the model to learn the nuances of language instead of relying solely on predefined rules.",
    "This approach has led to widespread applications of NNs in NLP tasks such as text classification, sentiment analysis, and language translation [42,15,64,59,47,8].Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) address the limitations of traditional feedforward Neural Network Language Models by incorporating recurrent connections, enabling them to capture complex temporal dependencies in sequential data [51,11,20].",
    "RNNs possess a \"memory\" mechanism facilitated by a recurrent matrix in the hidden layer, allowing them to retain information from previous time steps [51,48].",
    "This memory mechanism is crucial for processing sequential data such as natural language, where the meaning of a word often depends on its context within a sentence or document.",
    "This characteristic makes RNNs particularly well-suited for sentiment analysis tasks, where understanding the sentiment expressed in a text requires considering the relationships between words and their order within a sentence."
  ]
}